quizzes.question:
Fill in the blank to test both conditions in the following if statement.
[!raw!]
int age = 23;
int money = 4000;
if (age > 21 {0} money > 500) {
   System.out.println("Welcome");
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Logical Operators[/h1]

Logical operators are used to combine multiple conditions.

Let's say you wanted your program to output "Welcome!" only when the variable [b]age [/b]is greater than 18 and the variable [b]money [/b]is greater than 500. 
One way to accomplish this is to use nested [b]if [/b]statements:[code format="java" codeId="731"]if (age > 18) {
   if (money > 500) {
      System.out.println("Welcome!");
   }
}[/code]
However, using the [b]AND [/b]logical operator ([b]&&[/b]) is a better way:[code format="java" codeId="732"]if (age > 18 [b]&&[/b] money > 500) {
   System.out.println("Welcome!");
}[/code]
[note]If both operands of the AND operator are true, then the condition becomes true.[/note]

quizzes.question:
What is the output of the following code?
int a = 11; int b = 12;
int c = 40;
if (a > 100 || b > 3) {
  System.out.println(a); 
} else {
  System.out.println(c);
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The OR Operator[/h1]

The [b]OR [/b]operator (||) checks if any one of the conditions is true. 
The condition becomes true, if any one of the operands evaluates to true.
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="java" codeId="733"]int age = 25;
int money = 100;

if (age > 18 [b]||[/b] money > 500) {
   System.out.println("Welcome!");
}
//Outputs "Welcome!"[/code]
The code above will print "Welcome!" if age is greater than 18 [b]or [/b]if money is greater than 500.

The [b]NOT [/b]([b]![/b]) logical operator is used to reverse the logical state of its operand. If a condition is true, the [b]NOT[/b] logical operator will make it false.
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="java" codeId="735"]int age = 25;
if([b]!(age > 18)[/b]) {
   System.out.println("Too Young");
} else {
   System.out.println("Welcome");
}
//Outputs "Welcome"[/code]
[note]!(age > 18) reads as "if age is NOT greater than 18".[/note]
